&lt;p&gt;Toshiba Global Commerce Solutions is seeking a hands-on Senior Software Engineer to lead end-to-end solution delivery for major retail platforms.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role, you will own a (design, trade-offs, governance), active implementation (mentoring, code reviews, select hands-on features), and operational ownership (delivery sign-off, post-release support) of high-impact solutions, bridging business requirements to working implementations. You will drive Dual-Track Agile processes, guiding the Discovery Track for clarity and design exploration, and the Delivery Track to ensure quality, traceability, and measurable outcomes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate combines deep architecture expertise with hands-on coding, practical prototyping, and AI/agent workflow integration across the software lifecycle—from analysis and design to testing, documentation, and code generation. You will mentor teams, make critical technical trade-offs, and take full accountability for delivery sign-off and post-release support.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role requires strong retail platform domain knowledge (POS systems, store operations), cloud-native architecture experience, and fluency with generative and agentic AI tools to accelerate development while preserving architectural integrity. You will be a key driver of engineering excellence, ensuring solutions are both innovative and operationally robust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Instrument and leverage AI/agentic workflows to accelerate design, prototyping, code generation, test-case creation, specification drafting, and automated validation across the software lifecycle.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;AI-assisted development oversight, ethical compliance, and integration of generative AI tools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own end-to-end solution delivery across Discovery and Delivery Tracks, converting business needs into validated prototypes, formal designs, decomposed deliverables, and accepted technical implementations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the Discovery Track under Dual-Track Agile, rapidly prototyping and demoing solutions to validate feasibility and align stakeholders before full implementation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate discovery outcomes into delivery backlog items, ensuring design intent, architecture standards, and non-functional requirements are preserved throughout implementation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead architecture design and governance across products and integrations: produce ADRs, interface contracts, data models, sequencing diagrams, migration/rollback plans, and traceability matrices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as active technical lead in client engagements: facilitate workshops, present technical solutions, make trade-off decisions, drive approvals, and act as a subject-matter expert for assigned platform areas.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement and demo reference code or critical components, applying hands-on coding in modern retail platform stacks, reviewing and approving deliverables from implementation teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and enforce architecture standards, reusable integration patterns, and non-functional requirements (security, scalability, observability) across client solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mentor and upskill engineers and architects on AI-assisted development, Dual-Track workflows, specification-driven design, and platform best practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to platform and portfolio strategy, identifying reusable assets, API-first designs, and gaps requiring investment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own risk analysis and mitigation for architecture decisions, including backward compatibility, data integrity, and compliance constraints.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
